01:25:39.260 --> 01:25:42.020
And my point is not to equate LGBT rights movements

01:25:42.020 --> 01:25:43.220
with black civil rights.

01:25:43.220 --> 01:25:45.340
I am aware that being a white queer person

01:25:45.340 --> 01:25:47.020
is not in any way equivalent

01:25:47.020 --> 01:25:49.140
to living in the aftermath of slavery.

01:25:49.140 --> 01:25:50.700
I'm just saying that there's this tendency

01:25:50.700 --> 01:25:53.440
to sanitize history and to imagine

01:25:53.440 --> 01:25:55.980
that progress was smooth and bloodless,

01:25:55.980 --> 01:25:59.960
that consensus evolved organically, when it just didn't.

01:25:59.960 --> 01:26:02.420
And then people get the impression that current movements

01:26:02.420 --> 01:26:06.140
are somehow more militant than successful past movements

01:26:06.140 --> 01:26:07.380
when they just aren't.

01:26:07.380 --> 01:26:11.940
I am fighting what I see as a powerful, insidious,

01:26:11.940 --> 01:26:15.540
misogynistic movement, a cultural movement

01:26:15.540 --> 01:26:17.940
that was illiberal in its methods.

01:26:17.940 --> 01:26:22.940
And I believe absolutely that there is something dangerous

01:26:23.360 --> 01:26:26.540
about this movement and it must be challenged.

01:26:26.540 --> 01:26:28.420
Why is J.K. Rowling like this?

01:26:28.420 --> 01:26:32.080
Chapter seven, why is J.K. Rowling like this?

01:26:32.080 --> 01:26:35.700
J.K. Rowling loves to quote radical feminist Andrea Dworkin,

01:26:35.700 --> 01:26:38.700
whom I've already mentioned a couple times in this video.

01:26:38.700 --> 01:26:41.720
I myself favor violence, deeply.

01:26:42.620 --> 01:26:46.200
Dworkin is known for her extreme sex-negative views,

01:26:46.200 --> 01:26:47.680
which I don't agree with.

01:26:47.680 --> 01:26:49.520
But she was an interesting writer,

01:26:49.520 --> 01:26:53.360
one of those half-crazed savants who gets in your head,

01:26:53.360 --> 01:26:55.080
who you can't stop thinking about.

01:26:55.080 --> 01:26:59.320
In my opinion, Dworkin's best book is Right-Wing Women,

01:26:59.320 --> 01:27:02.680
published in 1983, the era of Phyllis Schlafly

01:27:02.680 --> 01:27:03.960
and Anita Bryant.

01:27:03.960 --> 01:27:07.300
Right-Wing Women is an analysis of why so many women

01:27:07.300 --> 01:27:09.560
are drawn to conservative politics,

01:27:09.560 --> 01:27:11.920
seemingly against their own interests.

01:27:11.920 --> 01:27:13.880
Anyone who's interested in understanding

01:27:13.880 --> 01:27:15.560
the gender-critical movement,

01:27:15.560 --> 01:27:18.480
a crypto-reactionary backlash disguising itself

01:27:18.480 --> 01:27:21.040
as feminism, should read this book.

01:27:21.040 --> 01:27:22.440
In Dworkin's analysis,

01:27:22.440 --> 01:27:24.780
the political right makes certain metaphysical

01:27:24.780 --> 01:27:27.740
and material promises to women that both exploit

01:27:27.740 --> 01:27:29.980
and quiet some of women's deepest fears.

01:27:29.980 --> 01:27:32.220
No one can bear to live a meaningless life.

01:27:32.220 --> 01:27:35.320
Women fight for meaning just as women fight for survival.

01:27:35.320 --> 01:27:39.080
And conservative politics promises women meaning.

01:27:39.080 --> 01:27:41.560
The right offers women a simple, fixed,

01:27:41.560 --> 01:27:45.200
predetermined social, biological, and sexual order.

01:27:45.200 --> 01:27:47.000
Form conquers chaos.

01:27:47.000 --> 01:27:48.840
Form banishes confusion.

01:27:48.840 --> 01:27:51.240
The gender-critical movement offers women

01:27:51.240 --> 01:27:54.540
a brutally simple understanding of sex and gender.

01:27:54.540 --> 01:27:57.960
A woman is an adult human female.

01:27:57.960 --> 01:28:01.320
Right-wing anti-trans activist Posie Parker

01:28:01.320 --> 01:28:03.600
has made this phrase into the motto

01:28:03.600 --> 01:28:05.480
of the gender-critical movement.

01:28:05.480 --> 01:28:08.760
Adult human female.

01:28:08.760 --> 01:28:11.200
It's on billboards, it's on t-shirts,

01:28:11.200 --> 01:28:14.240
it's on banners, signs, and tweets.

01:28:14.240 --> 01:28:17.440
Presented with the authority of a dictionary definition,

01:28:17.440 --> 01:28:21.080
it's rigid, it's orderly, it's immutable.

01:28:21.080 --> 01:28:24.340
There are no exceptions, there are no blurred lines,

01:28:24.340 --> 01:28:26.600
there can be no change.

01:28:26.600 --> 01:28:30.640
This mantra is a defense against the conceptual instability

01:28:30.640 --> 01:28:33.160
and chaos that gender-criticals fear.

01:28:33.160 --> 01:28:36.000
The same fear that once drove homophobic women

01:28:36.000 --> 01:28:37.480
like Anita Bryant.

01:28:37.480 --> 01:28:39.560
It's just biologically that God made mothers

01:28:39.560 --> 01:28:40.760
so that we could reproduce.

01:28:40.760 --> 01:28:43.800
Homosexuals cannot reproduce biologically.

01:28:43.800 --> 01:28:47.160
Erasing the concept of sex removes the ability

01:28:47.160 --> 01:28:50.320
of many to meaningfully discuss their lives.

01:28:50.320 --> 01:28:51.520
Dworkin says,

01:28:51.520 --> 01:28:53.440
Within the frame of male domination,

01:28:53.440 --> 01:28:56.320
there is a good reason for women to hate homosexuality,

01:28:56.320 --> 01:28:57.800
both male and female.

01:28:57.800 --> 01:29:00.520
Women are interchangeable as sex objects.

01:29:00.520 --> 01:29:03.280
Women are slightly less disposable as mothers.

01:29:03.280 --> 01:29:06.280
The only dignity and value women get is as mothers.

01:29:06.280 --> 01:29:08.680
Having children is the one social contribution

01:29:08.680 --> 01:29:10.060
credited to women.

01:29:10.060 --> 01:29:12.680
It is the bedrock of women's social worth.

01:29:12.680 --> 01:29:15.440
Without childbearing, women know they have nothing.

01:29:15.440 --> 01:29:17.920
Homosexuality for women means having nothing,

01:29:17.920 --> 01:29:19.600
it means extinction.

01:29:19.600 --> 01:29:23.180
Substitute transgenderism for homosexuality

01:29:23.180 --> 01:29:25.880
and you'll understand the gender-critical movement.

01:29:25.880 --> 01:29:29.440
J.K. Rowling's definition of woman is this.

01:29:29.440 --> 01:29:33.440
The woman is the producer of the large gametes.

01:29:33.440 --> 01:29:36.520
The producer of the large gametes.

01:29:36.520 --> 01:29:40.560
Rowling says her primary concern about young trans men

01:29:40.560 --> 01:29:42.840
is the loss of fertility.

01:29:42.840 --> 01:29:46.440
Homosexuality, its rise in public visibility,

01:29:46.440 --> 01:29:49.680
attempts to socially legitimize or protect it,

01:29:49.680 --> 01:29:51.360
makes women expendable.

01:29:51.360 --> 01:29:53.840
The one thing women can do and be valued for

01:29:53.840 --> 01:29:55.640
will no longer be valued.

01:29:55.640 --> 01:29:58.460
Male homosexuality is especially terrifying

01:29:58.460 --> 01:30:01.840
because it suggests a world without women altogether,

01:30:01.840 --> 01:30:03.960
a world in which women are extinct.

01:30:03.960 --> 01:30:06.800
This exact fear appears frequently

01:30:06.800 --> 01:30:08.400
in gender-critical rhetoric.

01:30:08.400 --> 01:30:10.920
Trans activists are erasing women.

01:30:10.920 --> 01:30:13.520
They're erasing biological sex.

01:30:13.520 --> 01:30:16.400
They're going to call us pregnant people.

01:30:16.400 --> 01:30:20.160
Confused girls are being robbed of their precious fertility.

01:30:20.160 --> 01:30:23.560
Trans women are going to replace biological women.

01:30:23.560 --> 01:30:26.680
As a woman, I feel threatened because biological men

01:30:26.680 --> 01:30:28.520
are aggressively replacing women.

01:30:28.520 --> 01:30:30.400
You will not replace us!

01:30:30.400 --> 01:30:33.920
Sometimes this paranoia ramps up to the point of obsession

01:30:33.920 --> 01:30:36.440
and the results can be dazzling.

01:30:36.440 --> 01:30:39.440
In September 2022, Maya Forstater,

01:30:39.440 --> 01:30:41.920
who you'll remember as the anti-trans activist

01:30:41.920 --> 01:30:44.880
whom J.K. Rowling came out as a TERF to defend,

