01:33:31.920 --> 01:33:34.280
But the concerns she has that are valid

01:33:34.280 --> 01:33:36.480
have nothing to do with trans people.

01:33:36.480 --> 01:33:38.680
And they definitely have nothing to do

01:33:38.680 --> 01:33:41.480
with an adorable cartoon alien.

01:33:41.480 --> 01:33:44.880
Honestly, reading this, I have some concerns.

01:33:44.880 --> 01:33:48.480
Concerns like, where is Maya's husband?

01:33:48.480 --> 01:33:49.960
I know she has one.

01:33:49.960 --> 01:33:53.320
Isn't raising children supposed to be a mutual project?

01:33:53.320 --> 01:33:57.040
No one should have to feel this alone, raising children.

01:33:57.040 --> 01:33:59.200
That is a valid concern.

01:33:59.200 --> 01:34:00.840
Oh my God, we actually found one.

01:34:00.840 --> 01:34:02.520
It's like finding El Dorado.

01:34:02.520 --> 01:34:04.240
A valid concern.

01:34:04.240 --> 01:34:06.240
A valid concern.

01:34:06.240 --> 01:34:07.520
Isn't what's going on here

01:34:07.520 --> 01:34:09.680
that Maya is taking legitimate feelings

01:34:09.680 --> 01:34:12.440
of being overburdened and underappreciated

01:34:12.440 --> 01:34:15.520
and displacing those feelings onto transgender people?

01:34:15.520 --> 01:34:18.720
This is exactly how the gender-critical movement recruits,

01:34:18.720 --> 01:34:22.280
by providing a scapegoat to frustrated women.

01:34:22.280 --> 01:34:24.040
It's not your husband's neglect.

01:34:24.040 --> 01:34:26.920
It's not the increasing atomization of society.

01:34:26.920 --> 01:34:29.120
It's not the indignities of aging.

01:34:29.120 --> 01:34:32.680
It's Tala, the non-binary alien,

01:34:32.680 --> 01:34:36.840
with its dungarees and smug aura of gender neutrality.

01:34:36.840 --> 01:34:41.520
Mumsnet is the hub of the resistance to non-binary cartoons.

01:34:41.520 --> 01:34:43.120
It's too much, these people are too much.

01:34:43.120 --> 01:34:44.700
Okay, we have to be serious now.

01:34:44.700 --> 01:34:48.940
The political right also promises women safety and security.

01:34:48.940 --> 01:34:51.740
For women, the world is a very dangerous place.

01:34:51.740 --> 01:34:54.220
The right acknowledges the reality of danger,

01:34:54.220 --> 01:34:55.700
the validity of fear.

01:34:55.700 --> 01:34:57.780
The right then manipulates the fear.

01:34:57.780 --> 01:35:00.180
Women fear and resent male violence,

01:35:00.180 --> 01:35:02.220
which they're most likely to experience

01:35:02.220 --> 01:35:04.340
from the men closest to them,

01:35:04.340 --> 01:35:06.980
boyfriends, husbands, and fathers.

01:35:06.980 --> 01:35:09.740
They're most likely to be killed by sexual partners.

01:35:09.740 --> 01:35:13.180
But the need to survive in a male-dominated society

01:35:13.180 --> 01:35:16.140
means that women's legitimate fears and resentments

01:35:16.140 --> 01:35:19.700
often cannot be directed at the men with power.

01:35:19.700 --> 01:35:22.500
Inevitably, this causes women to take the rage

01:35:22.500 --> 01:35:26.100
and contempt they feel for the men who actually abuse them,

01:35:26.100 --> 01:35:29.420
those close to them, and project it onto others,

01:35:29.420 --> 01:35:32.540
those far away, foreign, or different.

01:35:32.540 --> 01:35:34.460
And this displacement of rage

01:35:34.460 --> 01:35:38.100
is just transparently what's going on with J.K. Rowling.

01:35:38.100 --> 01:35:41.220
In her essay about sex and gender issues,

01:35:41.220 --> 01:35:44.660
Rowling speculates that trans men are transitioning

01:35:44.660 --> 01:35:47.220
to be the son her father wanted.

01:35:47.220 --> 01:35:49.220
I really felt the rejection of my father,

01:35:49.220 --> 01:35:50.380
and that is one of the things

01:35:50.380 --> 01:35:53.220
that maybe leads someone going into homosexuality.

01:35:53.220 --> 01:35:55.500
And she describes the lingering trauma

01:35:55.500 --> 01:35:57.700
from her first violent marriage.

01:35:57.700 --> 01:36:00.020
The marriage at this point has turned very violent

01:36:00.020 --> 01:36:01.380
and very controlling.

01:36:01.380 --> 01:36:05.180
And that, she says, is why she decided to speak out

01:36:05.180 --> 01:36:07.940
against the transgender movement.

01:36:07.940 --> 01:36:10.540
If you try to understand this rationally,

01:36:10.540 --> 01:36:12.700
it looks like a total non sequitur.

01:36:12.700 --> 01:36:14.660
But if you look at it emotionally,

01:36:14.660 --> 01:36:16.420
there's a kind of logic to it.

01:36:16.420 --> 01:36:18.540
The existence of the dangerous outsider

01:36:18.540 --> 01:36:20.860
always functions for women simultaneously

01:36:20.860 --> 01:36:24.700
